We are excited to announce, that starting Monday, September 14th, FREE MEALS will be available for ALL Students.

Breakfast and Lunch Service will remain the same, salad bar will stay in place and Ala carte will be available in Middle and High School. Extra entrees will have to be paid with lunch account.

This USDA has made all school meals temporarily free until further notice.

Families still need to turn in free and reduced applications as this no cost benefit can end at any time.

What is in a meal for Breakfast & lunch?
The following are school meal components:

‚óè Milk (fat-free or 1%, flavored milk or unflavored) ‚óè Meat/meat alternate (Cheese, Yogurt, Nut Butter, Legume etc.) ‚óè Bread/grains ‚óè Fruit* ‚óè Vegetables*

*Students are required to take ¬Ω cup of a fruit or vegetable to make a meal at breakfast and lunch.

School nutrition staff are trained to help students build a reimbursable, balanced meal. **

post_text:
Senior check-in school material

The process will be in the high school gymnasium on May 15 from 8:00-3:30 PM. The students will enter the Northeast gym door, ten students, at a time and walk single file with social distancing between them. The school staff will manage the parking lot and entrance door. All students are to remain in their cars until they are motioned to enter the building. The students will be dropping off computers and there will be boxes labeled by departments where students will return calculators, novels, College math scratch paper, and other school-issued materials, etc... Seniors will pick up senior award certificates, college research papers (Ms. Peterson) and eighth-grade personal letters to themselves (Ms. Moser) Students will exit out the Northwest door to the parking lot, where students will be expected to leave the school grounds.
